kend fieldtrips provide fellows with some time to explore the beauty of northern california program agendas that are complete with assigned curriculum for 2010 and 2011 are attached below to provide a sense of the thematic content and rigor of the fellowship program over the three week program participants will explore the definition of democracy be exposed to development theory examine the role of constitutionalism in developing democracies and study theories of democratic transition readings are assigned for each lecture to provide a survey of the academic literature pertaining to the topic 2010 draper hills summer fellows agenda 62.5 kb 2011 draper hills summer fellows agenda 311.6 kb search support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4610 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
